'''沙伦·特拉维克'''（{{lang-en|Sharon Jean Traweek}}）是一位[[美国|美国]][[科学知识社会学|科学知识社会学]]家，[[加利福尼亚大学洛杉矶分校|加利福尼亚大学洛杉矶分校]]副教授<ref name=Indiana>{{cite thesis |degree= Ph.D |last= Traweek |first= Sharon |date= 1982 |title= Uptime, downtime, spacetime, and power: an ethnography of the particle physics community in Japan and the United States |url= http://www.ibiblio.org/mpact/mpact.php?op=show_tree&id=2356 |publisher=  |oclc= 680612278 |access-date= 2020-11-02 |archive-date= 2016-03-03 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160303232137/http://www.ibiblio.org/mpact/mpact.php?op=show_tree&id=2356 |dead-url= no }}</ref>，主要的科普作品有《[[物理与人理|物理与人理]]——对高能物理学家社区的人类学考察》（''Beamtimes and Lifetimes: The World of High Energy Physicists''），介绍了[[粒子物理學|粒子物理學]]家的世界，被翻译为中文等多种文字<ref>{{citation | last1 = Latour | first1 = Bruno | last2 = Woolgar | first2 = Steve | author-link1 = Bruno Latour | author-link2 = Steve Woolgar | contribution = Postscript to second edition (1986) | editor-last1 = Latour | editor-first1 = Bruno | editor-last2 = Woolgar | editor-first2 = Steve | editor-link1 = Bruno Latour | editor-link2 = Steve Woolgar | title = Laboratory life: the construction of scientific facts | pages = 273–286 | publisher = [[Princeton_University_Press|Princeton University Press]] | location = Princeton, New Jersey | year = 1986 | origyear = 1979 | isbn = 9780691094182 | ref = harv | postscript = .}} Originally published 1979 in Los Angeles, by [[Sage_Publications|Sage Publications]]</ref><ref>{{citation | last = Rosser | first = Sue V. | contribution = Life in the lab | editor-last = Rosser | editor-first = Sue V. | title = The science glass ceiling: academic women scientists and the struggle to succeed | pages = 45–46 | publisher = Routledge | location = New York, New York | year = 2004 | isbn = 9780415945134 | ref = harv | postscript = .}}</ref><ref>https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Sharon_Traweek</ref><ref>https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&as_sdt=0%2C6&q=beamtimes+and+lifetimes&btnG=&o